function usage() {
    cat << EOF
Usage: $(basename "$0") [OPTS..] [PKG..] [-- GITARGS..]

Options:
    -f  Force git fetch (otherwise once an hour)
    -v  More verbose; e.g. show all parent branches
Dangerzone:
    --submit
        Updates or files required PRs (syncs local to origin/local).

PreReq:
- GITEAUSER configured: "$GITEAUSER"
- PKGS configured: ${PKGS[@]}
- Set up 'git-obs' and 'git-ibs' commands to refer to src.suse and src.opensuse.
- Set up 'osc' and 'isc' commands to refer OBS and IBS.
- Create empty 'obs' and 'ibs' subdirectories. We use them for cloning the repos.
- Login to src.suse and src.opensuse and fork the packages from pool/PKG.
  (or do it on the command line; the script will hint if a fork is missing)

  # We want to merge factory(FF) into the product branches (PN).
  #
  #      ...P1...P2
  # 	   ..FF
  #
  # We'd like to have P1==P2, but unfortunately we cant influence how fast
  # the products merge pending PRs. Additionally there's no guarantee that
  # FF (synced from src.opensuse) and the product branches share a common
  # history.
  #
  # Anyway, if we'd merge each product branch independently we'd separate
  # the branches. That's actually not wrong, but disguises that the separated
  # branches are actually the same:
  #
  #            +-----------merge(P1|FF)...
  #           /           /
  #      ...P1...P2   ..FF
  #                \      \
  #                 +------merge(P2|FF)...
  #
  # So we expect there's one "lead" product branch and all other product
  # branches are ancestors of (or equal to) the "lead" .
  #
  #      ...FF        ...FF'        ...FF''
  #           \            \             \
  #     ...O---P1---O---O---P2            merge(P2|FF'')
  #              \         /  \          /
  #   - old PR:   +_P1_PR_+    \        /    }
  #   + new PR:    \            +_P2_PR+      } on --commit only
  #   + amended PR: +_____P1_PR_______+      }
  #
  # We merge the "lead" (local) and file/amend it's PR (origin->parent).
  # The other branches we force reset (local and origin) to the "lead"
  # and file/amend their PRs.
  #
  # NOTE: Without --commit we will not move origin/ branches nor file
  #       PRs. We will just adjust the local branches to check whether
  #       changes are pending (whether --commit would amend or file new PRs).

Recognized PR targets are:
    obs: parent/leap*
    ibs: parent/slfo*

We skip "obs" per default because there are no leap* branches for our packages.
Use "-v obs all" to check obs.

Without PKG args it checks the core stack only (libsolv, libzypp, zypper).
Pass package names to check specific packages or use "all".

[If "-- GITARGS.." is passed, this git command is executed in all repos rather
checking it's status]
EOF
}
